>Dobry vecer, 
>
>dekuju za poslani, na oplatku posilam par prikladu, kde to 
>dela neco jineho, nez by melo. (Typicky chybovou hlasku :) ). 
>
>investigate(sin(x)+2*x)
  => sage: point((pi - arccos(2), 2*pi + sin(pi - arccos(2)) - 2*arccos(2)))
  (arccos(2) nepatri mezi RR , hodne netransparentni bug!!!!!)

>all_investigate(sin(x))  
  => jen pomocna fce (pro testovani samplu)

>investigate(log(x)+sin(x))
  => vyjimka zpusobena to_poly_solve=True (zachytit pres "try")
  => zachyceno (ale zpomalovani 30s -> 80s -> 160s -> ...)

>inflection_points(x)
  => vraci [(r1, r1), (c1, c1)], co by melo spravne vracet?

>investigate(sin(x^2)) 
  => uz funguje (ale jen 1 stat)

>
>-- ten "autozoom" mi nejak nefunguje: 
>viz 
>investigate(sin(x)) 
>a 
>investigate(sin(4*x)) 
>(to by teoreticky mel vyjit stejny obrazek s jinym popisem os, 
>nebo to spatne chapu?). 
  => jiz dodelano (v tomhle pripadu uz prepise osy)
